ights and assesses Luke's theology and its transference to its Hellenistic addressees. In contrast to present research trends, there is a clearer distancing of Luke from early Judaeo-Christianity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aQ hypothesis (Synoptics criticism). 4aLogienquelle. 4aLukasevangelium. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / New Testament.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR0 cprintz978311017434240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311090845940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110908459423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110908459/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GTRc2000d2014